# Implementation Plan - Path Initialization Logic

## Goal Description
Ensure path planning always starts relative to the character's actual position by waiting for a valid position detection before initializing the target.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> The character will not start moving immediately upon enabling "Path Trace". It will wait until the system detects the character's position on screen.

## Proposed Changes

### Core
#### [MODIFY] [PathPlanningTracker.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs)
- Modify [SelectNextTarget](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#802-877) logic:
    - Check if `_lastKnownPosition` is valid.
    - If valid, proceed with [FindClosestPathNodeIndex](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#925-948).
    - If invalid (Empty), **return immediately** and log a warning/info that it's waiting for position.
    - Remove the fallback logic that defaults to `pathNodes.FirstOrDefault()`.

## Verification Plan
1. Enable `Path Trace` without character visibility (e.g., covered by window).
2. Verify log shows "Waiting for character position...".
3. Reveal character.
4. Verify log shows "Synced to closest node: Index=X".
